.TH UDPSCOPE 1 "2024" "udpscope 1.0.1" "UDP Traffic Analyzer"
.SH NAME
udpscope \- Professional UDP traffic analysis and diagnostics tool
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B udpscope
[\fIOPTIONS\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
UDPScope is a network observability and diagnostics tool for UDP traffic
analysis on Linux systems. It provides comprehensive monitoring, analysis,
and reporting capabilities for system administrators to diagnose UDP-based
applications and services.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\fB\-\-port\fR PORT
UDP port to monitor (required)
.TP
\fB\-\-duration\fR SECONDS
Capture duration in seconds (default: 30)
.TP
\fB\-\-interface\fR IFACE
Network interface to monitor (default: any)
.TP
\fB\-\-json\fR
Output report in JSON format
.TP
\fB\-h, \-\-help\fR
Show this help message and exit
.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
.B sudo udpscope \-\-port 2456 \-\-duration 60 \-\-interface any
Monitor port 2456 for 60 seconds on all interfaces
.TP
.B sudo udpscope \-\-port 53 \-\-duration 30 \-\-interface eth0
Monitor DNS traffic on eth0 for 30 seconds
.TP
.B sudo udpscope \-\-port 51820 \-\-duration 10
Quick 10-second capture on port 51820
.SH REQUIREMENTS
Requires tcpdump and iproute2 for basic functionality.
For full features, install tshark and docker.io.
.SH FILES
.TP
.I /usr/bin/udpscope
Main executable
.TP
.I /usr/lib/python3/dist-packages/udpscope/
Python module
